CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Weakly Reciprocal

CERN-OHL-W v2

Copyright © 2026 K0WLY (Carl Cowley)

                                                                        
                                                                        
Preamble                                                                
                                                                        
CERN has developed this licence to promote collaboration among          
hardware designers and to provide a legal tool which supports the       
freedom to use, study, modify, copy and distribute hardware designs     
and products based on those designs. Version 2 of the CERN Open        
Hardware Licence comes in three variants: CERN-OHL-P (permissive);     
and two reciprocal licences: CERN-OHL-W (weakly reciprocal) and        
CERN-OHL-S (strongly reciprocal).                                       
                                                                        
The CERN-OHL-W is copyright CERN 2020. Anyone is welcome to use it,    
in unmodified form only.                                                
                                                                        
Use of this Licence does not imply any endorsement by CERN of any      
Licensor or their designs nor does it imply any involvement by CERN     
in their development.                                                   
                                                                        
                                                                        
1 Definitions                                                           
                                                                        
  1.1 'Licence' means this CERN-OHL-W.                                 
                                                                        
  1.2 'Compatible Licence' means                                        
                                                                        
       a) any earlier version of the CERN Open Hardware licence, or    
                                                                        
       b) any version of the CERN-OHL-S or the CERN-OHL-W, or         
                                                                        
       c) any licence which permits You to treat the Source to which   
          it applies as licensed under CERN-OHL-S or CERN-OHL-W       
          provided that on Conveyance of any such Source, or any       
          associated Product You treat the Source in question as being  
          made available under CERN-OHL-S or CERN-OHL-W as            
          appropriate.                                                  
                                                                        
  1.3 'Source' means information such as design materials or digital    
      code which can be applied to Make or test a Product or to        
      prepare a Product for use, Conveyance or sale, regardless of its  
      medium or how it is expressed. It may include Notices.            
                                                                        
  1.4 'Covered Source' means Source that is explicitly made available   
      under this Licence.                                               
                                                                        
  1.5 'Product' means any device, component, work or physical object,  
      whether in finished or intermediate form, arising from the use,   
      application or processing of Covered Source.                      
                                                                        
  1.6 'Make' means to create or configure something, whether by        
      manufacture, assembly, compiling, loading or applying Covered     
      Source or another Product or otherwise.                           
                                                                        
  1.7 'Available Component' means any part, subsystem, module or       
      device, whether in physical or digital form, that:               
                                                                        
       a) is generally available for purchase or free download, as      
          applicable, and                                               
                                                                        
       b) is not dependent on any licence that requires a Product       
          incorporating the Available Component, or firmware of such    
          a Product, to be provided under any of the conditions of      
          this Licence.                                                 
                                                                        
  1.8 'External Material' means anything (including Source) which:     
                                                                        
       a) is only combined with Covered Source in such a way that it   
          interfaces with the Covered Source using a documented         
          interface which is publicly available and which is stated not  
          to be itself Covered Source, and                              
                                                                        
       b) is not a derivative of or does not include any Covered        
          Source, or, if it does, it is solely to the extent necessary  
          to facilitate such interfacing.                               
                                                                        
  1.9 'Publicly Available' means that the information is generally      
      accessible to anyone and may be retrieved via the internet or     
      other means at no cost.                                           
                                                                        
  1.10 'Licensor' means any person who creates or modifies Covered      
       Source. A Licensor may also be a Licensee.                       
                                                                        
  1.11 'Licensee' means any person who exercises rights under this      
       Licence.                                                         
                                                                        
  1.12 'Convey' means to communicate or transfer.                       
                                                                        
                                                                        
2 Applicability                                                         
                                                                        
  2.1 This Licence governs the use, copying, modification, Conveying   
      of Covered Source and Products, and the Making of Products. By    
      exercising any right granted under this Licence, You irrevocably  
      accept these terms and conditions.                                
                                                                        
  2.2 This Licence is granted by the Licensor directly to You, and     
      shall apply worldwide and without limitation in time.             
                                                                        
  2.3 You shall not attempt to restrict by contract or otherwise the    
      rights granted under this Licence to other Licensees.             
                                                                        
  2.4 This Licence is not intended to restrict fair use, fair dealing,  
      or any other similar right.                                       
                                                                        
                                                                        
3 Copying, modifying and Conveying Covered Source                       
                                                                        
  3.1 You may copy and Convey verbatim copies of Covered Source, in    
      any medium, provided You retain all Notices.                      
                                                                        
  3.2 You may modify Covered Source, other than Notices.               
                                                                        
      You may only delete Notices if they are no longer applicable to   
      the modified Covered Source and You may add additional Notices     
      applicable to Your modifications.                                 
                                                                        
      You may Convey modified Covered Source (with the effect that      
      You shall also become a Licensor) provided that You:              
                                                                        
       a) retain Notices as required in subsection 3.1;                 
                                                                        
       b) add a Notice to the modified Covered Source stating that You  
          have modified it, with the date and brief description of how  
          You have modified it;                                         
                                                                        
       c) add a Notice to the modified Covered Source prominently       
          stating that it is released under this Licence and any        
          conditions added under section 8; and                         
                                                                        
       d) Convey the Source (or a written offer to make it Publicly     
          Available within twelve months) in a form or using a means    
          reasonably calculated to allow anyone to receive, read and     
          reproduce the Source using readily-available hardware,         
          reading that Source either directly from the storage medium    
          on which it is Conveyed, or with the aid of a suitable device  
          or system.                                                    
                                                                        
  3.3 You may Convey Covered Source in compiled or other final form     
      under the conditions of sections 3.1 and 3.2, provided that You  
      also Convey the equivalent Source under the conditions of         
      sections 3.1 and 3.2.                                             
                                                                        
                                                                        
4 Making and Conveying Products                                         
                                                                        
  4.1 You may Make Products, and/or Convey them, provided that You      
      ensure that each such Product:                                    
                                                                        
       a) bears a Notice on a suitable place (such as a visible label,  
          in the casing or documentation) stating the Covered Source    
          from which it was Made is available under this Licence, and   
          stating the name(s) of Licensor(s); and                       
                                                                        
       b) accompanies the Product with a copy of this Licence.          
                                                                        
  4.2 Where any Covered Source is not produced by You, any Licensor    
      retains all rights to their Covered Source.                       
                                                                        
  4.3 If You Make a Product containing Covered Source and You do not   
      release Covered Source, You must:                                 
                                                                        
       a) provide a written offer to make Covered Source available for  
          at least three years; and                                     
                                                                        
       b) state the location where Covered Source can be obtained.      
                                                                        
  4.4 You may Make Products that include Available Components and/or   
      External Material without being required to license them under    
      this Licence.                                                     
                                                                        
                                                                        
5 Research and Development                                              
                                                                        
  You may Make Products that are subject to this Licence solely for    
  research and development, without being bound by sections 4.1 and    
  4.2 provided such Products are not Conveyed.                          
                                                                        
                                                                        
